  sodium: 3 g
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/aubergine-linguine-with-chilli-a-57a1d12a77d68d03258b4568
cuisine: Italian
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Pre-heat your #grill{} to high. Boil a large #pot{} of water. Peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped) and finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped). Place the flat side of a large #knife{} on the @garlic{2%cloves} and press down firmly to release the skin. Remove the skin and then finely chop both the garlic and the @sun-dried tomatoes{2}.

Slice the @aubergine{1} in half lengthways. Slice each half lengthways again into four long strips. Remove the white spongy parts with your knife. Now chop the aubergine widthways into 1cm chunks.

Mix your aubergine with a splash of @olive oil{splash} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and spread on a #baking tray{}. Put this on the shelf closest to the grill and cook for around ~{15%minutes}, or until it is soft and slightly crispy around the edges.

In a #non-stick frying pan{}, fry your onion, garlic, sun-dried tomatoes and @chilli flakes{1/4%tsp} in a splash of @olive oil{splash} on medium heat until the onion is soft. This should take around ~{5%minutes} - be careful not to let the ingredients burn.

Cook the @wholewheat tagliatelle{180%g} in the boiling water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for around ~{11%minutes}, or until 'al dente', then drain.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle - taste it as you go to get it just right.

Add the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} to your garlic and onion mixture, together with a few grinds of @ground black pepper{} to taste. Let the mixture bubble on medium-low heat for around ~{5%minutes}, until you have a nice thick sauce.

Once your sauce has thickened up and your aubergine is cooked, stir it into your sauce.

Next, drop in your pasta. If you're feeling up to the task, then toss the ingredients together to mix them. If you don't fancy redecorating your kitchen, then you can always stir the ingredients instead. Taste for seasoning, and add a bit more salt or pepper if needed. Sprinkle over your parsley and the @hard Italian style cheese{3%tbsp}(grated). Voila!